cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for classifying tweets related to adverse drug reactions and medication intake. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and information retrieval. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Support Vector Machines, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of domain-specific features and sentiment analysis suggests the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) respectively. Finally, the paper also involves some computational linguistics, which falls under the sub-category cs.CY (Computational Linguistics).
